HEADWORD: Proctorage
<hw>Proc"tor*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Management by a
proctor, or as by a proctor; hence, control; superintendence; -- in
contempt.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The fogging <xex>proctorage</xex> of
money.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

